==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spent
<hw>Spent</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ecr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Exhausted; worn out; having lost energy or motive force.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now thou seest me⟦br⟧
<qex>Spent</qex>, overpowered, despairing of success.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Heaps of <qex>spent</qex> arrows fall and strew the ground.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Exhausted of spawn or sperm; --
said especially of fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spent ball</b></col>, <cd>a ball shot from a firearm,
which reaches an object without having sufficient force to penetrate
it.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sperre</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Sper</ent>⟦br⟧
